==English==
==={{initialism}}===
'''AD'''

#Latin ''[[anno Domini]]'', 'in the year of (our) Lord', used to specify years counting from the birth of Christ (AD 1).
#Assistant Director.

====Usage notes====
*'''AD''' is used before the year number. Thus correct usage is "AD 2000", not "2000 AD".
*Many authors prefer to use [[CE]] ([[Common Era]]), which avoids Christian bias.

